items.text:
I recently had a detailed conversation with Kurt Evans of Artist2Artist, one of the established actor showcase platforms, specifically around demo reels, self-tapes, and how casting actually encounters actors.

A few points from that discussion are worth sharing, because they clarify a lot of confusion I keep seeing among actors at different stages.

On demo reels:
Casting directors are not ignoring traditional demo reels. A professional demo reel is still exactly that ‚Äî the professional work you‚Äôve done, compiled into a roughly three-minute video. What matters is how that reel is structured.

Rather than one or two long scenes, the reel works best when it‚Äôs made up of multiple 20‚Äì30 second sections, each clearly showing a type you would naturally be called in for ‚Äî parent, authority figure, professional roles, etc. The goal isn‚Äôt to replace the reel, but to make it immediately readable. Realistically, a director may only watch about 20 seconds before deciding whether you fit, so clarity matters more than length.

On highly produced self-tapes:
We spoke about the rise of very cinematic, highly produced self-tapes ‚Äî essentially mini-movies. Kurt isn‚Äôt against production value. In fact, he shared an example where one panelist loved a highly edited tape, while another felt it looked more like a finished production than an audition.

The key point he emphasized is that the purpose of a self-tape or showcase submission is still to evaluate acting. Most actors audition two to three times a week. It‚Äôs neither realistic nor necessary to shoot a short film every time. What casting needs is a clear window into the performance. Overproduction isn‚Äôt a mistake ‚Äî it‚Äôs just not what casting is primarily judging.

On agents and casting access:
This is the part many actors misunderstand. Casting primarily encounters actors through agents. It‚Äôs not about gatekeeping or access ‚Äî it‚Äôs how the system functions. There‚Äôs a trust relationship between agents and casting offices.

In a traditional setting, a casting assistant may block off hours of time, receive hundreds of short submissions from agents, and narrow those down to about twenty strong fits. That‚Äôs how casting begins to connect with talent. Without representation, casting offices often have no way of knowing an actor exists.

What showcases like Artist2Artist aim to do is create a space where casting can watch actors work outside the volume and time pressure of the standard submission pipeline.

The takeaway from the conversation was straightforward:
For actors who want to be seen consistently in film and television, representation is the first gateway into that ecosystem.

Hello!

Currently at the start of the casting process for the workshop version of my show next September!

(including 2 presentation milestones in February and June - more production details upon invite)

If you are a queer identifying musical theatre performer and feel aligned with the piece I would love to have you!

Please keep this in mind if you are thinking of applying and know that your time and energy will be deeply appreciated in other ways. Hoping for this to be only the beginning!

Loooove,

Chris xx

items.text: Come audit this weekly class that takes place right here in Sandy on Monday, Tuesday, or Wednesday nights and take your ability to the next level. Every student performs in front of the class every week. What decides auditions is the quality of the audition tape and what determines the quality of your tape is your Understanding of BEATS and ACTIONS and equally important - YOUR ABILITY TO EMOTIONALLY BRING THE GOODS with simplicity and precision. Come sit in on a class to see what it's all about.

items.text:
12/12/25

(This Is My) Family (Short Film)

A Comedy about family dynamics

A family near breaking point, implodes in one night. 

Shooting April location TBC

Auditioning: We want to receive self tapes first and those who make it to the next stage, we would love in person auditions by late January of 2026. 

Travel Expenses paid

Student film being screened at The BFI and will be entered into film festivals

Elizabeth (50s-60s) - Narcissistic mother who dominates her kids' lives. She speaks her mind much to the reluctance of everyone around her..

Marie (30s-40s) - She‚Äôs in the middle of a mid-life crisis and she blames elizabeth as she thinks she‚Äôs not the perfect mother that she presents herself as. So Marie rebels against this supposed ‚Äòperfect family‚Äô.

Shaun (30-40s) - Shaun simply accepts his place in the world and has very little self respect. He is in a loveless relationship with his wife (Claire) however he does not rebel against her out of fear of living life alone in his 40s. Yet again every man has his breaking point. 

Clare (30s-40s) - Clare needs power and control, so she has found a man she can excerpt this power on (Shaun.) Clare and Elizabeth are very similar and therefore team up to inflate each other's egos at the expense of Marie and Shaun. 

Email: tylerbrownework@gmail.com for further details

Please only respond if you are based in England as our budget will not cover travel from abroad.

items.text:
We are casting confident, expressive individuals to appear as contestants/guests on a high-energy, unscripted talk show inspired by classic formats such as Jeremy Kyle and Jerry Springer.

The show will be hosted by massive influencer, who will take the role of the presenter, guiding conversations, mediating disputes, and attempting to resolve real or semi-scripted personal conflicts in an entertaining, fast-paced environment.

This is a performance-based role requiring strong personality, emotional range, and the ability to react naturally on camera.

Role Description ‚Äì Contestants / Guests

Selected participants will appear on the show as individuals involved in a personal conflict, relationship issue, family dispute, secret reveal, or moral dilemma. Scenarios may include (but are not limited to):

Relationship breakdowns or accusations

Love triangles or cheating allegations

Friendship or family fallouts

Hidden secrets or confrontations

Lifestyle or behavioural conflicts

You will be expected to:

Play a character or heightened version of yourself

Engage in open, confrontational, or emotionally charged discussions

React naturally to questions, accusations, and audience/chat interaction

Remain in character throughout the segment

Be comfortable with raised voices, dramatic moments, and comedic tension

Ideal Candidate

Aged 18+

Confident and expressive on camera

Comfortable with confrontation and emotional performance

Strong improvisation skills (acting experience is a plus, but not required)

Able to think quickly and respond naturally in live situations

Thick-skinned and comfortable being part of viral, high-reach content

Important Notes

This is entertainment content, not a real counselling or therapy show

Scenarios may be planned, semi-scripted, or improvised

Content will be broadcast live and clipped for social platforms (TikTok, Instagram, YouTube, etc.)

Applicants must consent to being filmed and distributed online

Compensation

Paid role

Rate dependent on role complexity, screen time, and experience

**Project Type:** Independent Short Film
**Location:** Vancouver, BC
**Shoot Dates:** March, 2026
**ROLE**
* **Indigenous / First Nations / M√©tis / Inuit female actor**

message.text:
David Reynolds returns for one reason.
To jump.

Years of military PTSD and childhood trauma have followed him home.
His battles are no longer fought outside.
They live in his head.
And no matter where he runs, there is no escape.

The bridge stands waiting.
Cold. Hard. Steel.
Resilient, yet weakened every time someone walks across it.
A mirror of the man standing before it.

David comes back broken.
Ready to end it.

Then he learns the truth.
He has a son.

For a moment, hope breaks through.

It does not last.

Grief and fury collide.
David turns outward, cleaning up the mess around him.
But his greatest enemy was never out there.

It was always himself.

David Reynolds.
And he will not go gentle.

#NoGentleGoodnight #DavidReynolds #IndependentFilm #UKFilm #BritishCinema #DarkDrama #PTSD #Trauma #MentalHealth #VeteranStories #Grief #Resilience #Homelessness #MenTalking #FilmInstagram #MovieReels #IndieFilm

CASTING CALL - Vancouver, BC 

Zariya, a 20 something from a small town. She embodies the duality of light and dark femininity, delicate yet strong. She has long dark hair and darker features. She is represented by the Sun card in Tarot. She is the light within the dark, a beacon of hope. 

Title: The Burden of Transformation

Writer/Director: Salom√© Mu√±oz 

Genre: Drama

Themes: Psychological, Dreamy, Comedy within a Tragedy

Shooting dates: January 20/21 2026

You receive: copy, credit and meal! 

This project is very theatrical and over the top, a background in theatre performance/stage acting is ideal but not required. 

If you are interested, please send me headshots and a resume via [s.munoz@infocusfilmschool.com](mailto:s.munoz@infocusfilmschool.com) and for more information look to @theburdenoftransformation on instagram! 

Thank you!

items.text:
## **CASTING CALL ‚Äì ‚ÄúTETRACHROMACY‚Äù (Short Film)**

**Project Title:** *Tetrachromacy*

**Genre:** Drama

**Location:** Vancouver, BC

**Shoot Dates:** December 29 & 30, 2025

**Compensation:** Indie film, great experience, Volunteer project (we are all volunteers, there‚Äôs no budget.)

Synopsis

*Tetrachromacy* follows **Nathan**, a photojournalist who loses his ability to see color after a head injury, leaving his world in stark black and white. One year later, he discovers that color returns only through AI-recreated images of his photographs. His life shifts when he encounters **Claire**, a woman in a yellow dress who appears vividly in color within his monochromatic reality, challenging his isolation and reshaping his sense of connection.

Role breakdown
NATHAN(Lead, 30s, male)

* A passionate photojournalist with a strong artistic eye
* Suffers from cerebral achromatopsia following a head injury
* Intelligent, introspective, emotionally reserved
* Slightly awkward when expressing feelings
* **Emotional arc:** moves from isolation and frustration toward wonder, openness, and human connection

**Notes:**

This is a subtle, performance-driven role. Actor must be comfortable conveying emotion through restraint, stillness, and internal conflict.

Submission Details

Please submit:
* Headshot
* Resume (or relevant acting experience)
* Demo reel (if available)
* A short Self-tape

**Submit to:** [s6films.co@gmail.com](mailto:s6films.co@gmail.com)

**Submission Deadline:** December 21, 2025

If selected auditions will be hosted on December 22, 2025

Who we are:

S6 films is a a group of passionate filmmakers pursuing creating films we care about amidst busy life and jobs in video production.

items.text:
Dieses Erkl√§rvideo (KI generiert) ist ein Auszug, vielleicht eher eine verk√ºrzte Zusammenfassung, des Buches "HAGIA SOFIA, Siehst Du noch den Wei√üen Turm", und enth√§lt sowohl narrative Kapitel als auch umfangreiche Quellenangaben und formale Abschnitte. Die fiktive Haupthandlung dreht sich um eine Gruppe von Protagonisten, darunter die Historiker 

Elias und Nikos sowie Geheimdienstagenten, die versuchen, einen 

verheerenden Terroranschlag des sogenannten "Schattenkonvents" auf die Hagia Sofia in Thessaloniki zu verhindern, wobei die "Sonne von Vergina" als Code-Botschaft dient. Sixteen-year-old Noah has spent weeks drifting from everyone he loves,

## **üé≠ Casting Breakdown: *****OUROBOROS***

A Psychological Horror film. The Fourth Film from Pineal Dreams Productions.

‚ÄúWhen a young couple suffer the pain of a miscarriage; they retreat to a cottage in the woods to try and heal. Unfortunately they quickly discover that you can never run away from your trauma‚Äô

**DONN**

**Male | Playing age: 30-40 | Ethnicity: Open**

**Description:** Amaia‚Äôs partner. Kind, supportive, but emotionally shut down. A man attempting to cope through suppression - a misguided attempt at stoicism as he believes she must be strong to support Amaia - whose quiet unraveling becomes key to the resolution.

 **Performance notes:** Understated emotionality. Requires physical performance (injury, crawling, etc.) and strong presence in silence.

 **Comparable roles:** Michael Fassbender (*Shame*), Mads Mikkelsen (*Another Round*), Javier Bardem *(Mother!)*, Harry Dean Stanton *(Paris, Texas)*

Filming block will be the same as Amaia‚Äôs. Five-day block (Hopefully), as well as shoots at just three other locations.Ten days of filming maximum, but this could always change if re-shoots are necessary, and one day of ADR work will be required.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

PAID - A minimal fee. Which can be discussed upon application. This is our fourth short-film, and the first we‚Äôve offered payment for. It was a late decision, as we appreciate experience doesn‚Äôt pay the rent. However, being a tiny, self-funded studio, it is a relatively small amount.

All food and transport - and accommodation, if needed - also covered.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

**üë• Supporting Roles -**

**THE UMBRA**

**Male | Playing age: ANY | Tall, slender, distinctive presence | Ethnicity: Open**

 **Description:** A silent manifestation of trauma that watches over and manipulates events ‚Äî a mythic observer of Amaia‚Äôs trauma. Symbol of death, memory, or fate.

 **Performance notes:** No dialogue for a vast majority of the script, though requires a sequence of some very carnival-esque dialogue. Face never seen. Must convey gravitas, mystery, and quiet threat through stillness and gaze.

 **Type:** Dancer, mime, or physical performer backgrounds welcomed. Could even opt for the possibility of a physical performer, and a separate voice-actor. So any voice-actors interested, please feel free to contact us.

Similar Roles: Doug Jones (Pan‚Äôs Labyrinth), Tim Purcell (The Babadook), Javier Botet (Slenderman)

The Umbra appears in the Cottage and scenes surrounding it, all of which will be filmed during the scheduled five-day filming block.

There will also be one additional day, in which you will be required for a single scene that takes place in a different location.

Re-shoots are of course always possible, and will be needed for one ADR session for dialogue provided during an animated sequence.

PAID - But a smaller fee than Amaia/Donn as will be required for less days.  This can be discussed upon application. We aim to film a bulk of the filming in one five-day block, with one scene needing filming elsewhere. We anticipate filming will require tsix days, with one day of ADR needed for additional dialogue/audio fixes.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

We are a very small studio, and this is our fourth short. However, our mantra has always been a ‚Äòquality over quantity‚Äô approach. We take great pride in not just making a film, but really thinking it through on a technical level. We appreciate classic and arthouse cinema, and are far more interested in making a good film than red carpet events.

Our three shorts so far have been screened at over 20 festivals, picking up around 14 awards - including two IMDB qualified awards. (best actor for Jackson Wright in Inside The Abyss). Our latest film has seen our lead - Tash Morley - pick up three awards. We aim for this to be our best film yet.

If interested in the roles, please contact me directly via the Pineal Dreams Instagram page. My own personal profiles - both Joshua Moulini√© (Facebook/Instagram). Or Email me directly on [Moulinie23@gmail.com](mailto:Moulinie23@gmail.com)

We hope to hear from you all very soon!

I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that‚Äôs been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we‚Äôll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Maybe you feel an ex-partner or family member has taken more than their fair share? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you‚Äôd like the free advice of some of Britain‚Äôs top lawyers (likely in region of ¬£10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

items.text:
Hello!

Currently at the start of the casting process for the workshop version of my show next September!

(including 2 presentation milestones in February and June - more production details upon invite)

If you are a queer identifying musical theatre performer and feel aligned with the piece I would love to have you!

PS. Please note this is a university funded production and due to guidelines I am not allowed to pay anyone for their time. Please keep this in mind if you are thinking of applying and know that your time and energy will be deeply appreciated in other ways. Hoping for this to be only the beginning!

Loooove,

Chris xx

items.text:
The Cottage
By Sandy Rustin
Directed by Ben Green
Auditions:
Monday, January 5, and Tuesday, January 6 at @ 7:00pm
Callback by invitation on Wednesday January 7 @ 7pm

Play Overview:
A fast-paced, heightened comedic farce set in 1923 England. Infidelity, mistaken identities, exaggerated manners, and bold physical comedy drive the show. All roles require strong comedic timing, physicality, and the ability to deliver heightened, crisp dialogue in a British dialect.

The director encourages diverse casting. No role has a strict requirement of ethnicity or race.

Physicality & Intimacy: Farcical timing, comedic blocking, and in some roles intimacy scenes (kissing / romantic chemistry) are required; also comedic violence or slapstick may appear.

As the play is set in 1923 England: RP / British accent is required.

Character Breakdown:
Sylvia
Gender: Female
Age: Mid-20s to 40s
Description: A ‚Äúlovely and rash romantic.‚Äù Sylvia is impulsive, passionate, and clings to romantic idealism. She‚Äôs the one who initiates the comedic uproar by deciding to reveal her affair which triggers the farcical unraveling of secrets.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should embody flirtatious charm, emotional volatility, and physical energy. Expect moments of passion/intimacy (kissing or romantic touch) and heightened comedic reactions or slapstick. 

Beau
Gender: Male
Age: Mid-20s to late 40s
Description: Beau is described as ‚Äúperhaps the best-looking man in Britain.‚Äù He‚Äôs charming, handsome, and somewhat complacent. A man comfortable with the status quo, even when his romantic life is scandalous. His affair with Sylvia is marked by both desire and hesitation.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should have presence, charm, and ease. Needs comfort with intimacy (romantic scenes) and comedic timing, especially with farcical elements. RP British accent.

Marjorie
Gender: Female
Age: Mid-20s to 40s (she is very pregnant in the play)
Description: Beau‚Äôs wife. ‚ÄúEight months pregnant, pragmatic‚Äù, grounded, and composed, even in the face of shocking revelations. Underneath, she has a sharp edge; she‚Äôs ‚Äúa tad spicy.‚Äù 
Physical / Performance Notes: You will be wearing an insanely pregnant-belly. Needs emotional range: from shock to self preservation to possible betrayal or strength. Comedic instincts + ability to react strongly to chaos.

Clarke
Gender: Male
Age: Mid-20s to late 40s
Description: Sylvia‚Äôs husband. A refined, ‚Äúdistinguished gent with a lover‚Äôs spirit.‚Äù He may appear respectable and stable, but underneath, his loyalties and feelings are complicated. Entangled in the web of affairs and deceptions.
Physical / Performance Notes: Needs a balance of dignity and vulnerability. Believable as a gentleman, but also capable of comedic panic or confusion. Comfortable with farce pacing and quick reaction work. 

Dierdre
Gender: Female
Age: Early 20s to 30s (or thereabouts, though exact age is flexible)
Description: She‚Äôs described in the script as ‚Äúan awfully pretty, sometimes wise, nincompoop.‚Äù She‚Äôs na√Øve, sweet, perhaps a bit ditzy, but also occasionally offers piercing insight. She often reacts to the chaos with bewilderment and innocence, which amplifies the comedy.
Physical / Performance Notes: Needs to deliver endearing innocence, comedic timing, and willingness to play ‚Äúditzy‚Äù with heart. Should be comfortable with exaggerated reactions, physical comedy and the heightened energy of farce. 

Richard
Gender: Male
Age: 30s to 50s
Description: A dark comedic twist in the farce. Richard is described as ‚Äúmurderous‚Äù but ‚Äúgentle,‚Äù meaning he occupies the role of destabilizing danger amidst the comedic chaos. His arrival triggers tension, threat, and unexpected comedy. A perfect blend of menace and absurdity.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should be able to handle heightened dramatic tension and farcical comedy. Perhaps a little brooding, but also capable of shambling comedy or over-the-top melodrama. Must be okay with comedic threat, possibly physical acting (gun or
threat).

Bring a headshot and resume and be ready to list ALL conflicts.

Performances: February 27 to March 22, 2026
Rehearsals Begin January 12 at Cabrillo Playhouse
All genders, body types, and ethnicities are encouraged to audition

items.summary:
The Cottage
By Sandy Rustin
Directed by Ben Green
Auditions:
Monday, January 5, and Tuesday, January 6 at @ 7:00pm
Callback by invitation on Wednesday January 7 @ 7pm

Play Overview:
A fast-paced, heightened comedic farce set in 1923 England. Infidelity, mistaken identities, exaggerated manners, and bold physical comedy drive the show. All roles require strong comedic timing, physicality, and the ability to deliver heightened, crisp dialogue in a British dialect.

The director encourages diverse casting. No role has a strict requirement of ethnicity or race.

Physicality & Intimacy: Farcical timing, comedic blocking, and in some roles intimacy scenes (kissing / romantic chemistry) are required; also comedic violence or slapstick may appear.

As the play is set in 1923 England: RP / British accent is required.

Character Breakdown:
Sylvia
Gender: Female
Age: Mid-20s to 40s
Description: A ‚Äúlovely and rash romantic.‚Äù Sylvia is impulsive, passionate, and clings to romantic idealism. She‚Äôs the one who initiates the comedic uproar by deciding to reveal her affair which triggers the farcical unraveling of secrets.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should embody flirtatious charm, emotional volatility, and physical energy. Expect moments of passion/intimacy (kissing or romantic touch) and heightened comedic reactions or slapstick. 

Beau
Gender: Male
Age: Mid-20s to late 40s
Description: Beau is described as ‚Äúperhaps the best-looking man in Britain.‚Äù He‚Äôs charming, handsome, and somewhat complacent. A man comfortable with the status quo, even when his romantic life is scandalous. His affair with Sylvia is marked by both desire and hesitation.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should have presence, charm, and ease. Needs comfort with intimacy (romantic scenes) and comedic timing, especially with farcical elements. RP British accent.

Marjorie
Gender: Female
Age: Mid-20s to 40s (she is very pregnant in the play)
Description: Beau‚Äôs wife. ‚ÄúEight months pregnant, pragmatic‚Äù, grounded, and composed, even in the face of shocking revelations. Underneath, she has a sharp edge; she‚Äôs ‚Äúa tad spicy.‚Äù 
Physical / Performance Notes: You will be wearing an insanely pregnant-belly. Needs emotional range: from shock to self preservation to possible betrayal or strength. Comedic instincts + ability to react strongly to chaos.

Clarke
Gender: Male
Age: Mid-20s to late 40s
Description: Sylvia‚Äôs husband. A refined, ‚Äúdistinguished gent with a lover‚Äôs spirit.‚Äù He may appear respectable and stable, but underneath, his loyalties and feelings are complicated. Entangled in the web of affairs and deceptions.
Physical / Performance Notes: Needs a balance of dignity and vulnerability. Believable as a gentleman, but also capable of comedic panic or confusion. Comfortable with farce pacing and quick reaction work. 

Dierdre
Gender: Female
Age: Early 20s to 30s (or thereabouts, though exact age is flexible)
Description: She‚Äôs described in the script as ‚Äúan awfully pretty, sometimes wise, nincompoop.‚Äù She‚Äôs na√Øve, sweet, perhaps a bit ditzy, but also occasionally offers piercing insight. She often reacts to the chaos with bewilderment and innocence, which amplifies the comedy.
Physical / Performance Notes: Needs to deliver endearing innocence, comedic timing, and willingness to play ‚Äúditzy‚Äù with heart. Should be comfortable with exaggerated reactions, physical comedy and the heightened energy of farce. 

Richard
Gender: Male
Age: 30s to 50s
Description: A dark comedic twist in the farce. Richard is described as ‚Äúmurderous‚Äù but ‚Äúgentle,‚Äù meaning he occupies the role of destabilizing danger amidst the comedic chaos. His arrival triggers tension, threat, and unexpected comedy. A perfect blend of menace and absurdity.
Physical / Performance Notes: Should be able to handle heightened dramatic tension and farcical comedy. Perhaps a little brooding, but also capable of shambling comedy or over-the-top melodrama. Must be okay with comedic threat, possibly physical acting (gun or
threat).

Bring a headshot and resume and be ready to list ALL conflicts.

Performances: February 27 to March 22, 2026
Rehearsals Begin January 12 at Cabrillo Playhouse
All genders, body types, and ethnicities are encouraged to audition
There is a small stipend offered

items.text:
Altarena Playhouse (Alameda, CA) is holding auditions for *‚ÄòNight Mother *by Marsha Norman, Directed by ShawnJ West

 

Performance Dates: May 29th through June 28th     

(Fridays/Saturdays at 7:30 pm, and Sundays at 2:00 pm)

 

SHOW SYNOPSIS:

Thelma Cates is a mother and widow who lives with her daughter, Jessie. Jessie is the divorced mother of a troubled son who struggles with life as an unemployed epileptic. She confesses to her mother that she is going to take her life. Tonight. As Mama pleads with her to reconsider her decision, old secrets are revealed, and long-ignored feelings rise to the surface. The mother-daughter bond between Jessie and Mama becomes stronger and lovelier than ever, making it possible for Jessie to end her noisy, cluttered existence, and take a quieter, calmer path with closure and love.

 

AUDITION DATES:

Monday, January 19th at 7:00pm and Saturday, January 24th at 1:00pm, by appointment

 

Callbacks: Monday, February 2nd, 7-10 pm, by invitation

 

Rehearsals begin April 25, 2026 at 11:00 am

 

Auditions will be held at the Altarena Playhouse, 1409 High Street, Alameda

 

Performers of all races, ethnicities, and genders are encouraged to audition.

 

Non-AEA only. $500 Reimbursement for expenses

 

 

CHARACTER DESCRIPTIONS:

THELMA ‚ÄúMAMA‚Äù CATES (Female, 60s)

Warm, talkative, and steeped in the routines of her home life, Thelma is a woman who uses chatter, caretaking, and small comforts to keep the world steady. Beneath her practical exterior, she carries deep anxieties, regrets, and unspoken guilt that surface as the night unfolds. Actors should bring emotional dexterity, humor grounded in truth, and the ability to navigate sharp tonal shifts as Mama confronts an unthinkable situation with both denial and fierce love.

 

JESSIE CATES (Female, 40s)

Direct, methodical, and emotionally contained, Jessie is a woman who has lived with chronic illness, disappointment, and a profound sense of futility. She speaks plainly and acts with quiet determination, revealing a grounded pragmatism rather than melodrama. Actors should bring a nuanced stillness, clarity of intention, and the ability to reveal the powerful internal life beneath Jessie‚Äôs calm, steady presence.

 

To sign up and for audition sides, visit:  [https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night](https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night)

 

Please contact Katina at [artisticdirector@altarena.org](mailto:artisticdirector@altarena.org) should you have any questions.

items.text:
STUDENT SHORT FILM CASTING 

Shooting dates: 23rd-25th January

Location: Vancouver, North Vancouver

Volunteer, lunch and copy of film provided. 

**MARTY (20-25)**
* A young pianist struggling with anxiety and health issues. His passion for music is strong, but he is haunted by self-doubt and physical limitations. Emotionally vulnerable, he carries the weight of the past, yet despite the toll on his body and mind, he persists in pursuing his dreams.

**MARTY'S MOTHER (40s-50s)**
* A supportive, hard-working single mother. Cares deeply for her son and masks her worries about his skill with a calm, composed demeanor, despite the mental and physical toll it‚Äôs taking on her.

**SUBMISSION**

Please send:
* Headshot or recent photo
* Short bio or acting resume (if available)

Shortlisted candidates will be invited to an audition, January 7th. If unavailable, a self-tape will be accepted. 

**Submit to:** melodymovie2026@gmail.com

AUDITONS FOR RAG DOLLY - THE RAGGEDY ANN MUSICAL WORKSHOP 

Seeking actors for a public workshop reading of Rag Dolly. In Rag Dolly, a little girl named Marcella is dying of a mysterious illness. Her father makes her a rag doll to comfort her, and his stories of the doll come to life in her dreams to guide her through her grief and fear. Marcella and her new friends confront wolves, witches, and incompetent doctors on their way to outwit death and mend her broken heart.

**PAID** Hi everyone! We are currently casting for WISP, a haunting coming-of-age drama about isolation, queer longing, and the grip of an unseen presence.

To be Shot in: West Yorkshire.

 

Synopsis:

Sixteen-year-old Noah has spent weeks drifting from everyone he loves,

manipulated by an unseen presence. When his best friend Sam turns up on New Year‚Äôs Eve, Noah finds himself caught between feelings he‚Äôs long buried and the Voice that refuses to let him go.

 

Characters:

NOAH (16‚Äì25, male) ‚Äì Quiet, introspective, emotionally guarded. Must be able to convey internal conflict, subtle fear, and vulnerability with restraint.

SAM (16‚Äì25, male) ‚Äì Warm, intuitive, and grounded. Noah‚Äôs best friend; emotionally open, present, and deeply human.

 

Shooting: 12/2 ‚Äì 15/2   (Night Shoots)

Payment: TBD ‚Äî we are happy to discuss this with you.          

 

üì© Contact: [jaxon.s.murtagh@gmail.com](mailto:jaxon.s.murtagh@gmail.com) with Showreel if available. Script will be available.

Please feel free to share or tag anyone who might be interested.  üå≥üñ§

items.text:
**CASTING CALL!!!**

We are casting for a new tour of the children‚Äôs theatre show, ‚ÄúTom Gates Live‚Äù, based on the popular book series by Liz Pichon.

The show is written and directed by Miranda Larson with songs and music by Barrie Bignold and is produced by Mark Thompson at MT Productions.

Rehearsals begin on 19th January ‚Äì 29th January 2025 in London.
Tour dates Jan ‚Äì Oct 2026. We are currently have 65 tour dates and counting.
**ROLE: Tom Gates**

Tom Gates is an easily distracted and creative 10-year-old boy who loves doodling, listening to music, and annoying his older sister, Delia.

He is best friends with Derek, and they share a passion for music, with dreams of becoming rock stars in their band, DogZombies.

We are looking for a musical theatre performer that can sing, perform slapstick and comedy, and can perform the role of a young boy.

Within the show, there is basic singing, dancing and movement but nothing too technical.

The successful applicant will need to be comfortable assisting with the load ins/ outs and have a full UK drivers licence as they will be asked to assist driving the touring van

Playing age: 16 years - 23 years

Gender: Male

**Contract info:**

Rehearsal fee: ¬£550pw

Show day fee: ¬£150

Travel day fee: ¬£50

Subsistence: ¬£20

Please send cv's and headshots to *casting.mtproductions@gmail.com*

items.text:
**Perfect Xmas Gift for Actors! *****‚ÄúTHE ACTOR'S MANIFESTO: Create a Successful Acting Career‚Äù*** Amazon Books--blends techniques, neuroscience, psychology, and industry business savvy to help actors master the craft and the industry in USA.

**What it covers:**

The Craft: Deep dives into realism in acting, key techniques and modern approaches.

The Psyche: Strategies for managing an actor's mental state.

The Business: Advice on navigating the entertainment industry.

Science: Neuroscience on how acting works in the brain.

Holistic Approach: Skill, mental health, and business acumen.

 

Written by Linda Ann Watt, SAG-AFTRA, AEA Member, SAG-AFTRA Signatory Producer/Director, MFA in Theatre Pedagogy, and 2015 Tony Award Nominee for Education. This book bridges theory and the demands of an acting career. **TheActorsManifesto.org**

Celebrated as ‚Äúheart-touching‚Äù and praised for her ‚Äúbrilliant stage presence,‚Äù she enchants audiences in the USA, the UK, and across Europe ‚Äì and will return to Australia on tour next year.

Bernhard Lehner accompanies masterfully on piano.

AUDITION ANNOUNCEMENT - URGENT! 

**UNPAID** 

AUDITION NOTICE ‚Äì Curious Incident of the Dog in the Nighttime, adapted by Simon Stephens, based on the novel by Mark Haddon.

Directed by Roger Beaumont for The Questors Theatre.

Performances Friday, 20th March ‚Äì Saturday 28th March 2026 

The Questors Theatre, W5 5BQ London. 

Audition dates: 

Monday, 22 December, 2025, 7pm 

Tuesday, 23 December, 2025., 7pm 

About the play:

‚Äò*Curious''* tells the story of 15-year-old neurodivergent Christopher Boone, who investigates the death of a neighbour's dog, and uncovers a web of lies that leads him to discover his mother is alive, not dead as he was told, and that his father killed the dog. Overwhelmed by his father's deception, Christopher runs away to London to live with his mother, a journey that involves navigating a terrifying and confusing new world. The play ends with Christopher taking and passing his A-level maths exam in London, showing he can achieve anything he sets his mind to, and beginning to repair his relationship with his father. 

Christopher experiences ‚Äòsensory overload‚Äô when exposed to unfamiliar places and situations and finds it hard to express his emotions, even to his parents. He also struggles to understand facial expressions and body language. He excels at maths and sciences and like his hero, Sherlock Holmes, relies on logic to make sense of the world around him. 

Character: 

1M late teens to mid twenties - Christopher 

Please email me on robinsonfeatures@gmail.com if you'd like to attend. 

An amateur production by arrangement with Concordetheatricals

**UNPAID**

Hey everyone! I‚Äôm currently casting for my upcoming short film, *After the Rain*, an intimate emotional drama about two sisters navigating the aftermath of their mother‚Äôs sudden death. When a violent storm forces Mia and Isla back together, unspoken grief and buried pain rise to the surface, pushing them toward understanding, healing, and renewed connection.

To be shot in: High Wycombe/ London 

**Synopsis:**

After their mother‚Äôs sudden death, two sisters are pulled apart by grief, distance, and unspoken pain. Mia, the older sister, leaves to pursue a promising job opportunity, trying to outrun the heartbreak of their loss. Isla stays behind, sinking into isolation and self-destructive behaviour as her distress deepens. When Mia returns on a stormy night to find Isla drunk and unravelling, the sisters are forced to confront years of buried resentment and abandonment. Through raw confessions and shared vulnerability, they begin a journey towards understanding, forgiveness, and the possibility of hope, finding solace in the quiet strength of sisterhood. 

Characters:

**ISLA (19-22, FEMALE)** 

impulsive, reckless, emotionally unstable little sister. Must be able to portray internal conflict and intoxication.  

**MIA (25-28, FEMALE)**

protective, compassionate, responsible older sister. Must be able to portray internal conflict and the effects of grief. 

Shooting: DATES TBC  (approx JAN 6-16th)    

If interested, please contact me for more information at austenfilmworks@gmail.com 

Please feel free to share or tag anyone who might be interested. üé•üé¨

**Perfect Xmas Gift for Actors! *****‚ÄúTHE ACTOR'S MANIFESTO: Create a Successful Acting Career‚Äù*** Amazon Books--blends techniques, neuroscience, psychology, and industry business savvy to help actors master the craft and the industry.

**What it covers:**

The Craft: Deep dives into realism in acting, key techniques and modern approaches.

The Psyche: Strategies for managing an actor's mental state.

The Business: Advice on navigating the entertainment industry.

Science: Neuroscience on how acting works in the brain.

Holistic Approach: Skill, mental health, and business acumen.

 

Written by Linda Ann Watt, SAG-AFTRA, AEA Member, SAG-AFTRA Signatory Producer/Director, MFA in Theatre Pedagogy, and 2015 Tony Award Nominee for Education. This book bridges theory and the demands of an acting career. **TheActorsManifesto.org**

ROLE: Mother

AGE: 45‚Äì55

ETHNICITY: Open (Eastern European/Ukrainian accent is a strong plus, but not required)

LANGUAGE: English (accent acceptable)

PROJECT: ANXIETY (Short Film)

GENRE: Psychological Drama

FORMAT: Indie / Non-Union

LOCATION: Toronto, ON

ROLE DESCRIPTION:

The Mother is a grounded yet emotionally complex woman. Protective, conflicted, and deeply connected to her son. She carries unspoken worry and subtle strength. This role requires emotional depth and strong presence rather than heavy dialogue.

SHOOT DETAILS:

 ‚Ä¢ 1 shooting day (January 24, 2026)

 ‚Ä¢ Non-paid indie project

 ‚Ä¢ Meals & craft services provided

 ‚Ä¢ Festival submissions planned

 ‚Ä¢ Short film with potential expansion into a feature

SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS:

Please send:

 ‚Ä¢ Headshot

 ‚Ä¢ Resume or acting portfolio

 ‚Ä¢ Demo reel or self-tape (optional but preferred)

üì© Email: anxietyfeaturefilm@gmail.com

Subject line: Mother ‚Äì Your Name

This is the casting call for my short film, Metalhead, its a project that I'm very passionate about and my hope is that you may be to.

Filming in stoke in January.

This is my 5th filmmaking project, and I really would like to take this opportunity to push the envelope when it comes to working with actors and drawing out performances.

If either of these roles stand out as a role that would suit you, please don't hesitate to get in touch at cian4472@hotmail.co.uk

VOLUNTEER ONLY

This is a student production, and unfortunately I don't have the budget to be able to pay crew or cast. I am more than happy to pay for expenses and catering for contributors.

items.summary:
This is the casting call for my short film, Metalhead, its a project that I'm very passionate about and my hope is that you may be to.

Filming in stoke in January.

This is my 5th filmmaking project, and I really would like to take this opportunity to push the envelope when it comes to working with actors and drawing out performances.

If either of these roles stand out as a role that would suit you, please don't hesitate to get in touch at cian4472@hotmail.co.uk

VOLUNTEER ONLY

This is a student production, and unfortunately I don't have the budget to be able to pay crew or cast. I am more than happy to pay for expenses and catering for contributors.
